race.description: John Deere Breeder Cup Juvenile Turf Stakes (G1)
race.comment: PRECISE (13) looks a very exciting filly on the rise, bolting in to score the Fillies' Mile at Newmarket most recently. She did it from the back of the field there, so suspect Soumillon to adopt similar tactics from a tricky draw today. Looks a cut above her rivals and is clearly the one to beat. QUEEN OF HAWAII (2) sat handy and was too good at the Curragh last start when winning at G3 level. She'll need to raise the bar again to match precise, but she'll have all the advantages close to the speed. Has upside and can build on what she did last time out. TIME TO DREAM (9) has jumped the fave in her past two, finishing 1.1L away last start in the Jessamine when getting a long way back. Suspect Irad will look to have her closer this time around and with some luck, she'll go close. GROUND SUPPORT (11) sustained a long run to score the Miss Grillo last start and has strong claims. IMAGINATIONTHELADY (3) looks a horse on the rise and can feature from a better draw today.
